spanGrp.span: Mãĩ komĩ estee pekaga sẽr-gẽ ska
He had a lot of apples planted;
Je rö jie-wa wã esteee… pekaga wã mansana/ je të mansana tka tã'ĩ jeska
so he climbed up a tree to bring them down.
ñerö jie mẽnẽu í (m) jula jãrga mansana bötsö
When he was up on the apple tree’s branch, a child came by on his bike and took a basket full of ripe apples.
ñerö jie ka (_) ka/ ka/ jie kateröga mãĩ mãĩ estee… mansana jula ska Ñerö yaba dajũ-te bisikleta inga (_) (_) jaba mẽnẽtse je (_) je (_) jaba jaba mẽnẽtse shëlita estee mansana ebö
As he was going away uh… a girl was coming;
Ñerö mãĩ damĩũ komĩ ra estee peyaba busi dajũ
so he turned to see her and thus did not see the stone before him so his bike crashed against it;
ñerö je wöchá-mĩ í sũã Ñerö ka jie-wa jak sunẽ í wö tsõ ñerö je mẽnẽu-te nẽ (_) bisikleta mẽnẽu té-nã esteee… jak mẽ
So there were other children who came to help him pick up the apples.
Jeke/ je batamẽra estee… mãĩ yabla datse (hm) të í kimã' estee í mansana shtöga
They put the apples back in the basket and then they left.
je jiá-wã-ite í jaba jãrga Ñerö etabaglö í yaba yaba mẽnẽu-mĩ-nẽ
They got to where the hat was lying and one of them shouted at him and ran toward him to hand it over to him.
Mãĩ yaba mẽnẽu-mĩ mãĩ sombrero jatanã'-wã je juã' yaba anã' í tsaga Ñerö je mẽnẽu tu-lë í juã' ĩã
Then the child paid him back with three apples;
Ñerö mãĩ estee… yaba të í patuã' estee (_) mansana mã'-ite mãñã-l
one for each because there were three kids.
Je rö e-gla e-gla ĩã porke jie-wa rö mãñã-l
Next the man came down and picked up the apples
Ñerö mãĩ estee pekaga jẽk jawã-te të të í mansana shtá
but noticed that a basket was missing;
kai mans/ (_) ñera jaba shenã ĩã e-gla
only one of them was full; the other one wasn’t.
(_) E-gla ka rö shi e-gla bö rö shi-ñẽ-ra
So he realized that the apples were missing.
Ñerö pekaga të sũã'-ra kai mansana jue-nã
So the children threw the hat at him and went back.’
ñerö yabla (m) të sombrero juã' ĩã Ñerö jie-wa beteu-lo-te
